================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY
================================================================================

C++ header:         include/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpRec.h
C++ implementation: src/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpRec.cpp

Purpose: Typed emStructRec schema for a tree-dump node — Frame enum,
BgColor, FgColor, Title, Text, Commands (array of {Caption, Args}),
Files (array of strings), and Children (recursive array of
emTreeDumpRec). This is the in-memory record type that the in-app
renderer (emTreeDumpFilePanel / emTreeDumpRecPanel) loads from a
saved .emTreeDump file and walks to paint zoomable nodes.

Status: NOT PORTED — in-app dump-renderer subsystem out of scope for
the current dump-producer work (Phase 1 of
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-24-treedump-port-design.md).

The Rust port only needs to *produce* .emTreeDump files, not consume
them as a typed schema for in-app rendering. crates/emcore/src/emTreeDump.rs
assembles the schema inline via RecStruct field writes (Frame, BgColor,
FgColor, Title, Text, Commands, Files, Children) rather than through a
typed mirror of emTreeDumpRec. The producer side has no structural need
for a typed struct; only the reader side (emTreeDumpFilePanel) does,
and that reader is not ported.

Rust equivalent for now: the inline RecStruct field assembly in
crates/emcore/src/emTreeDump.rs. The schema (field names, types, order,
Frame enum values) is byte-identical to the C++ emTreeDumpRec schema
so the written files are interchangeable with C++ Eagle Mode.

Future port path: if/when the in-app dump-renderer subsystem is ported
(emTreeDumpFilePanel + emTreeDumpRecPanel + emTreeDumpFileModel), a
typed emTreeDumpRec mirror can be added mechanically at that point,
since the schema is already fixed.
